{
  "texts": [
    "When inspected individually, even human experts cannot determine their nature easily.",
    "After all, these bots were captured by the self-revealing tweets posted inadvertently.",
    "Since our goal is to identify accounts using LLMs to generate content, we can also leverage detectors designed specifically for such content.",
    "Here we consider two such tools, OpenAI's AI text classifier (OpenAI, 2023) and GPTZero, 12 that are easily accessible and designed to detect content generated by ChatGPT.",
    "In January 2023, OpenAI released their AI text detector, 13 a language model fine-tuned on human-and machine-generated content that works for different LLMs including OpenAI's own models."
  ]
}